{"title_page": "Indian Institute of Management Sambalpur", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=September 2018}}\n{{Infobox university\n| name = Indian Institute of Management Sambalpur\n| native_name = \n| native_name_lang = or\n| image = IIM Sambalpur.jpg\n| established = 2015\n| type = [[Public school (government funded)|Public]] [[business school]]\n| chairperson = [[Arundhati Bhattacharya]]\n| director = Mahadeo Jaiswal<ref>{{cite web|title=Director's Message - IIM Sambalpur|url=http://www.iimsambalpur.ac.in/about-us/directors-message/|website=IIM Sambalpur|accessdate=16 November 2017}}</ref>\n| students = \n| address = Sambalpur University Campus, Jyoti Vihar, Burla\n| city = [[Sambalpur]]\n| state = [[Odisha]]\n| postalcode = 768019\n| country = [[India]]\n| coordinates = {{coor|21.485578|83.879457}}\n| campus = Urban\n| website = {{url|https://iimsambalpur.ac.in/}}\n}}\n\n'''Indian Institute of Management Sambalpur''' is a public business School located in [[Sambalpur]], [[Odisha]], India. It is one of the [[Indian Institutes of Management]]. The first batch of students started in September 2015.\n\nCurrently the institute is hosting its 5th batch of 2019\u20132021. The present campus of IIM Sambalpur is situated at Sambalpur University Campus, Jyoti Vihar, Burla, Sambalpur, Odisha.\n\n==History==\nIIM Sambalpur was announced in 2014 by [[Ministry of Human Resource Development]] (MHRD)<ref name=bs>{{Cite web|title = IIM-Sambalpur takes off with 48 students|url = http://www.business-standard.com/article/management/iim-sambalpur-takes-off-with-49-students-115092300947_1.html|accessdate = 2015-10-27}}</ref> and was established in 2015.{{citation needed|date=April 2019}} The first batch of students started in September 2015.<ref name=bs/>\n\nIt was initially mentored by IIM Indore until appointment of its independent director. IIM Sambalpur was registered as a Society under Societies Registration Act, XXI of 1860 on August 19, 2015. The present campus of IIM Sambalpur has been set up at Jyoti Vihar, Burla, Sambalpur, Odisha.\n\nIIM Sambalpur has been allotted a piece of land measuring over 237 acres in Basantpur, for the permanent campus by the Government of Odisha.\n\nDuring the mentorship period, IIM Sambalpur's recruited its own faculty and was frequented by guest  faculty members from various IIM's and premier Institutes.\n\nCurrently its headed by Mahadeo Jaiswal as the director.\n\n==Campus ==\nIIM Sambalpur is functioning from its temporary campus at [[Sambalpur University]].<ref>{{cite web |title=IIM Sambalpur At a Glance |url=http://www.iimsambalpur.ac.in/about-us/iim-sambalpur-at-a-glance |website=www.iimsambalpur.ac.in |accessdate=21 April 2019}}</ref> The campus houses the one academic block, canteen, hostels, and an auditorium.\n\nThe Government of Odisha has selected 237 acres of land for the construction of the permanent campus of IIM Sambalpur at Basantpur.{{citation needed|date=April 2019}}\n\nIn 2018, the Government of India proposed a budget of {{INRConvert|400|c}} for facilitating the construction of the permanent campus and is expected to be ready by 2022.{{citation needed|date=April 2019}}\n\n=== Student accommodation ===\nStudents are provided single room accommodation in the 33 fully furnished [[Dormitory|dormitories]] spread across the campus.\n\nThere are three hostel buildings inside the campus of the institute; two for boys and one for girls. The students of IIM Sambalpur are provided rooms on a twin-sharing basis.\n\nThe rooms are properly ventilated and well furnished with a bed, almirah, mattress, study-tables and chairs provided to each student. Housekeeping staff maintains the cleanliness of the rooms on a daily basis.\n\nHigh-speed Wi-Fi has been made available which is accessible from anywhere within the campus premises. Each hostel also has a separate common room where a TV and table tennis facilities are installed to cater to the recreational needs of the students.\n\nCurrently there's no provision for Married students so they cannot opt to live with their family in hostels. Stay in dormitories is mandatory for students. Basic amenities including washing machines, refrigerators and TVs are available at each dorm.\n\n==Academics==\nIIM Sambalpur offers various postgraduate diplomas in management. Admission is based on [[Common Admission Test]] conducted jointly by the IIMs and on various other processes conducted by IIM Sambalpur.<ref>{{cite web |title=Admissions |url=http://www.iimsambalpur.ac.in/programmes/post-graduate-programme-in-management/admissions |website=www.iimsambalpur.ac.in |accessdate=21 April 2019}}</ref>\n\nLike other IIMs, IIM Sambalpur currently offers master's degree in management as per the approval of the [[Indian Institute of Management Bill, 2017]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/education/cabinet-approves-iim-bill-2017/|title=Cabinet Approves IIM Bill|accessdate=4 February 2017|publisher=Indian Express}}</ref> These include two-year full-time programmes (PGP),<ref>{{cite web|url=https://iimsambalpur.ac.in/programmes/post-graduate-programme-in-management|title=Programme - IIMA|last=|first=|date=|website=iimsambalpur.ac.in|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|accessdate=23 November 2019}}</ref> one-year full-time residential programme for experienced professionals (PGPX),<ref>{{cite web|url=https://iimsambalpur.ac.in/pgpx|title=About PGPX - IIM Sambalpur|last=|first=|date=|website=iimsambalpur.ac.in|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|accessdate=23 November 2019}}</ref> and also offers doctoral level fellowship programmes.<ref name=\"iima.ac.in2\">{{cite web|url=https://iimsambalpur.ac.in/phd/about-programme|title=FPM|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|accessdate=1 January 2020}}</ref> The institute conducts a number of executive education and faculty development programmes.\n\n=== Exchange programmes ===\nIIMSAM has affiliations with one leading business schools that is Alba Graduate Business School, Greece and in talks with reputed foreign B-Schools for possible collaboarations. The students of IIM Sambalpur who partake in the exchange program would spend an entire trimester at the host University at no additional academic fees. The agreement allows for the exchange of a limited number of students who are selected on the basis of their interests and a screening process. As a first step of the collaboration between the two premier B-Schools, IIM Sambalpur sent two of its students for a four-day Summer B-School program in Athens. The students learned about the Greek economy, Greek philosophy, visited multiple industries and corporate offices and were taken to some of the famous historical sites in Athens.\n\n=== Admission ===\nIIM Sambalpur offers different academic programs and has admission processes and eligibility respectively. Its process is based on the course candidate opt for. [[Common Admission Test|CAT]] score is the basic exam to apply for admission in all of the academic programs. Total seats are further divided into the category where IIM accept admission on the category basis. Good academic record and percentage score is another major aspect.\n\nIIM's also conducts its analytics writing test and personal interview (AWT & PI) in Ahmedabad, Banglore, Hyderabad, Kolkata, & New Delhi cities of selected candidates. Seats in IIMSAM are reserved, based on government instruction 27% of seats are reserved for NC-OBC,  15% for SC, 7.5% for ST candidates, 5% for Persons with Benchmark Disabilities (PwD), and up to 10% for Economically Weaker Sections (EWS).\n\n== Events ==\n\n=== Marmagya ===\nMarmagya is the Annual Business Conclave of the Indian Institute of Management Sambalpur. Over the years, Marmagya has been gaining momentum to become a platform that brings together industry leaders, budding entrepreneurs, inspiring personalities, and motivated students to discuss, debate and recalibrate.\n\n=== Ethos ===\nEthis is the annual cultural festival of IIMSAM. Its yearly editions have been centred on themes like diversity, colour or going green. The cultural festivities draws footfalls of around 5,000 visitors from Sambalpur over three days and participation from institutes across the country. Pro-nites (events hosted by professional artists) are especially a huge success with a large number of top class artists coming and performing on one stage.\n\n=== Other events ===\nBallyhoo Street\n\n== Placements ==\nThe placement process at IIM Sambalpur is a student-driven process that institutionalizes placements for the entire batch. The Placement Committee elected by the students liaisons between the Institute administration, students and recruiters. Placements for the PGPs are characterised by two phases - summer placements for the first-year batch and final placements for the graduating batch. The summers process is conducted in Nov/Dec for the first yearites. The second year placement committee handles the process for them. The placement process for the graduating is conducted in two stages. The first is the laterals process in January where firms interview students with prior work experience and offer them mid-level managerial positions. The second stage is the final placement process in around February. This process is handled by the newly elected committee among the PGP1s to avoid any conflict of interest and ensure a fair process. Companies from multiple sectors across different geographies hire candidates for a wide range of functions.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Indian Institutes of Management}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Business schools in Odisha]]\n[[Category:Universities and colleges in Sambalpur]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 2015]]\n[[Category:2015 establishments in India]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=Se